# Elite Fitness Image Asset Checklist

To replace the placeholder/temp images with real photos of your 2,000 sq.ft boutique gym, here is a complete checklist organized by where they appear on the website. Use this as your photography shot list!

## 1. Global (Appears on every page)
- **Primary Logo:** ([/asset/Logo.png](file:///j:/clints/Elite%20fitness%202/asset/Logo.png)) - Needs to be a transparent PNG of the "Elite Fitness Clubb" logo.

## 2. Home Page (`/`)
*The Home page needs your highest-end, most "wow" factor images.*
- **Hero Carousel Banner:** 4 high-quality landscape photos to cycle through at the very top. Currently: `Pillar 1.jpeg`, `Pillar 2.jpeg`, `Pillar 3.jpeg`, `Pillar 4.jpeg`.
- **Bento Box (Elevate Your Potential):** 
  - Image for "ELITE TRAINERS" cell.
  - Image for "BOUTIQUE SETUP" cell.
  - Image for "THE GYM FLOOR" cell.
  - Image for "COMMUNITY & RECOVERY" cell.
- **Bottom Call to Action Background:** ([/asset/Sitting area wall.jpeg](file:///j:/clints/Elite%20fitness%202/asset/Sitting%20area%20wall.jpeg)) - A wide, cinematic shot of the gym ambiance.

## 3. Services Page (`/services`)
*These images should clearly illustrate people engaging in the specific services.*
- **Service 01: Elite Personal Coaching:** Focus on a trainer working 1-on-1 with a client.
- **Service 02: Strength & Conditioning Floor:** A wide or dynamic shot of the main lifting area and premium equipment.
- **Service 03: Group Fitness & HIIT:** Action shot of a Zumba or high-energy group class.
- **Service 04: Premium Recovery & Ice Bath:** High-quality photo of the Ice Bath or Sauna/Recovery zone.

## 4. About Us ("Boutique Manifesto") Page (`/about`)
*This page tells your specific story.*
- **Top Hero Image:** A very dark, aesthetic, and clean wide shot of the empty gym floor.
- **Founder's Portrait:** A highly professional, confident photo of you (the owner/head coach). It should be vertical/portrait, high contrast, matching the "Visionary" theme.
- **The Elite 10 (Coaches Carousel):** You will need 10 individual, professional headshots/action-shots of your coaching team.

## 5. Membership Page (`/membership`)
*These are the small pop-up preview photos that appear when someone hovers over the features in the Comparison Grid.*
- **Strength & Cardio Floor:** Mini-preview image.
- **Group Classes (Yoga, Zumba):** Mini-preview image.
- **Diet & Nutrition Consult:** Photo of the Cafe / Consultation office.
- **Personal Trainer Sessions:** Mini action shot.
- **Ice Bath Recovery Zone:** Mini preview shot.

## 6. Explore Hub (Virtual Tour & Gallery) (`/explore`)
*The gallery requires a high volume of diverse shots. Group them into these buckets:*
- **Gym Interior / Floor:** General clean shots of the facility (Pillars, lighting, layout).
- **Equipment Details:** Close-ups of weights, machines, barbells (Macro/aesthetic shots).
- **Classes / Action:** Photos of Yoga, Zumba, and people actively working out.
- **Recovery & Amenities:** Ice bath area, Cafe wall, Sitting area, Men's Changing Room, Female Changing Room.

## 7. Contact Page (`/contact`)
- **Contact Hero Background:** A dark, moody background image of the gym floor, strictly to add texture behind the contact form.

> [!TIP]
> **Photography Advice:** For the premium, "Boutique" look, avoid bright, washed-out fluorescent lighting. Ask your photographer to use high-contrast, moody lighting, focusing on the equipment, the neon accents, and the cleanliness of the 2,000 sq ft space. Always export final images in **.webp** format for lightning-fast website speeds!
